Author: lilsofish
Text: that could be a possibility i hadn't considered! i always thought that wouldn't be something i'd have to worry about bc she's been 10-20lbs lighter than me for quite some time (if anything, i usually find myself jealous of her) but you may be on to something.   perhaps, she's afraid i'll catch up to her quickly and continue to lose while she plateaus. i'll try not to let her comments get to me in the future and watch what i say as well. thanks for shedding some light on that!

Author: coffeecreamer06
Text: She sounded like she was actually jealous of you and like she got triggered? I have a sister and we both have disordered eating. We trigger each other over the smallest miscommunications.
